five sample opinions

[1] I think this speech shows an interesting way to see life. In many places, people believe that winning is the most important goal. However, in Japan, as the speaker describes, people play to enjoy the game and to make others feel good. I like how everyone changes partners and does not keep score. This makes everyone feel like a winner, even if they don’t win every point. It also teaches us that teamwork and kindness are as important as personal success. This idea could make sports and even life happier for everyone.                                                                                                    
[2] I think not to emphasise the winning is important, because if I emphasise it, I can’t enjoy the game well. If you want to enjoy the game, not to care much about winning or losing. And I think, the thing which is assumed to be important is not only winning or losing in the game. I think that Japanese think the behaviour after finishing the game is very important, rather than not emphasising the winning or losing. Then, I agree that not getting ahead isn't the same thing as falling behind. To walk together is important, and it creates an emotional bridge, so I think we don’t have to feel that we are falling behind.
[3]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             
[4]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             
[5] I really agree with the idea that Japanese people play ping-pong without thinking of the score. I also play ping-pong with my family, friends and so on with joy. It makes us get along well. To do something together, especially sport, earns a good relationship of trust.
